        <article><![CDATA[<p>The Custom Chat Integrations framework of scriptable APIs allow you to bring ServiceNow chat to any conversational interface of your choice.</p>
<p>To create your own custom adapter, you will need to:</p>
<ul style="list-style-position: inside;"><li>Define your own provider (also known as Connections, e.g. Twilio).</li><li>If necessary, define a corresponding channel (e.g. SMS). Please note that a channel can support multiple providers. </li><li>Create action scripts that will allow the transformation between ServiceNow chat components and your adapter display.</li></ul>
<p>You can find more details <a title="here" href="https://docs.servicenow.com/bundle/quebec-performance-analytics-and-reporting/page/administer/virtual-agent/task/create-adapter-for-virtual-agent.html" rel="nofollow">here</a> for the steps to create your own adapter and <a title="action scripts" href="https://docs.servicenow.com/bundle/quebec-performance-analytics-and-reporting/page/administer/virtual-agent/reference/va-action-scripts.html" rel="nofollow">action scripts</a>. A developer might be required to complete the following steps. </p>]]></article>
